  "text": "where J H 2 is the hydrogen flux permeating through the membrane, Pe H 2 the hydrogen permeability, δ the membrane thickness, p H 2,retentate and p H 2,permeate the hydrogen partial pressures in the retentate and permeate zones, respectively, and n (varying between 0.5-1) is the dependence factor of the hydrogen flux on the hydrogen partial pressure. In the case of dense Pd-based membranes having thickness higher than 5 µm, Equation (4) Housing a Pd-based membrane in a MR, the enhancement of the reaction conversion with respect to the equivalent conventional reactor is promoted by the so-called \"shift effect\" [CITATION_1] . Indeed, the hydrogen perm-selectivity characteristics of Pd-based membranes allow for the enhancement of conversion due to the hydrogen removal from the reaction toward the shell side.",
